                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d607">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">611.5831/132</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">Memorandum by the Secretary of State</hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">[<placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>,] <date calendar="gregorian" when="1934-10-11">October 11,
                            1934</date>.</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>The Swedish Minister called and delivered to me a memorandum, of which the
                    attached is a copy,<note n="17" xml:id="d607fn17">
                        <hi rend="italic">Infra.</hi>
                    </note> relating to proposed trade agreement negotiations between our two
                    governments. I thanked him and replied <pb facs="0821" n="721" xml:id="pg_721"/>
                    that I and my associates would give the subject matter of his memorandum the
                    fullest and most careful attention and consideration.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>C[<hi rend="smallcaps">ordell</hi>] H[<hi rend="smallcaps"
                        >ull</hi>]</signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
